public abstract class MessageMapAtomicGroundingImpl<T>
extends AtomicGroundingImpl<T>

Yet another layer of abstraction to be subclassed by atomic groundings that use input and output message maps.

getMessageMap

protected final MessageMap<T> getMessageMap(Parameter p)
Utility method to be used by subclasses. It iterates either through the input message maps (p instanceof Input) or the output message maps (p instanceof Output). Each mapping is checked if its parameter is equal to the given parameter. If so, this message map will be returned.

getMessageMap

protected final MessageMap<T> getMessageMap(boolean inputs,
                                            java.lang.String uri)
Utility method to be used by subclasses. It iterates either through the input message maps (inputs == true) or the output message maps (inputs == false). Each mapping is checked if its MessageMap.getGroundingParameter() (which is actually a URI) is equal to the given URI. If the URIs do not fully match but they contain a fragment identifier those fragments will be compared alternatively. As soon as either the full URIs match or the fragment identifiers, the message map will be returned.

removeMessageMaps
